ree so parallel\n3220:  workers do not share Gradle daemons, but reuses one shared Gradle wrapper\n3222:  `FORGE_GRADLE_DISTRIBUTIONS_HOME` to override that cache location, or\n3223:  `FORGE_GRADLE_USER_HOME` to override the full Gradle user home.\n3229:  directly when debugging a single task or reproducing a failure.\n3298:  Forge is located inside `graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge`. The parent checkout is the default reachability repository, and successful run metrics are written under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`. Top-level automation still creates one detached metadata-repo worktree per issue run; the run's pending metrics root is the same worktree's `forge/` directory (§WF-forge-workflow-drivers, §FS-durable-generation-logs).\n3320:  ### Fix javac test failures for a new library version\n3326:  - Run Gradle tests and, if native test fails, collect metadata and re-run.\n3335:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage] \\\n3345:  - `--metrics-repo-path`: optional path to the metrics root. If omitted, the `forge/` directory in the selected worktree is used.\n3354:    --metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage \\\n3363:  - Runs Gradle tasks inside the reachability-metadata repo (`./gradlew ...`).\n3364:  - On success, writes metrics into `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json` (§FS-durable-generation-logs).\n3382:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage] \\\n3391:  - `--metrics-repo-path`: optional path to the metrics root. If omitted, the `forge/` directory in the selected worktree is used.\n3399:    --metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage \\\n3409:  - Runs Gradle tasks inside the reachability-metadata repo (`./gradlew ...`).\n3410:  - On success, writes metrics into `<metrics_repo_path>/new_library_support/results.json` (§FS-durable-generation-logs).\n3424:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics_repo_root]\n3433:    --metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics_repo_root\n3438:  - Run after the fix_javac_fail.py workflow has produced a successful result and metrics (§GIT-forge-publication).\n3451:    [--metrics-repo-root /path/to/metrics_repo_root]\n3459:    --metrics-repo-root /path/to/metrics_repo_root\n3464:  - Run after the add_new_library_support.py workflow has produced a successful result and metrics written under `<metrics_repo_root>/new_library_support/results.json` (§GIT-forge-publication).\n3466:  ### Pipeline: Fix javac test failures + PR creation\n3478:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics_repo_path] \\\n3495:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics_repo_path] \\\n3508:  - Record per-run metrics under the configured metrics repository (in `benchmark_run_metrics/`).\n3521:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage] \\\n3528:  - `--metrics-repo-path`: optional path to the metrics root. If omitted, the `forge/` directory in the selected worktree is used.\n3565:  - Metrics writer:\n3567:    import utility_scripts.metrics_writer as metrics_writer\n3569:    run_metrics = metrics_writer.create_run_metrics_output_json(\n3579:    metrics_writer.append_run_metrics(run_metrics, \"output/results.json\")\n3585:    from utility_scripts.schema_validator import validate_run_metrics\n3587:    validate_run_metrics(\"output/results.json\")\n3594:    - `run_metrics_output` validates run metrics output files using `../stats/schemas/run-metrics-output-schema-v1.0.1.json`:\n3596:      python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py run_metrics_output output/results.json\n3598:    - `benchmark_run_metrics` validates benchmark run metrics files using `schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json`:\n3600:      python3 utility_scripts/schema_validator.py benchmark_run_metrics /path/to/benchmark_run_metrics.json\n3616:  - For Git/PR automation: keep commit messages clear, include the target library coordinates, and reference the metrics produced by the workflow.\n3619:  - If a script performs technical changes to the graalvm-reachability-metadata repository (tests, metadata, Gradle tasks, CI logic), implement and contribute that logic in that repository.\n3643:      \"after-failed-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/after-failed-iteration/basic_after_fail.md\"\n3648:      \"max-failed-generations\": 4,\n3664:  coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\n3665:  failure output in normal prompt templates.\n3699:  The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n3705:  Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n3744:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage] \\\n3755:    [--metrics-repo-path /path/to/metrics-storage] \\\n3765:    `python3 ai_workflows/drivers/fix_javac_fail.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]`\n3767:    `python3 ai_workflows/drivers/add_new_library_support.py --coordinates <group:artifact:version> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>]`\n3768:  - Open PR with metrics:\n3769:    `python3 git_scripts/make_pr_javac_fix.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo-root>]`\n3771:    `python3 git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py --coordinates <group:artifact:version> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-root <metrics-repo-root>]`\n3773:    `python3 complete_pipelines/fix_javac_create_pr.py --coordinates <group:artifact:old> --new-version <newVersion> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]`\n3775:    `python3 complete_pipelines/add_new_library_support_create_pr.py --coordinates <coordinates> [--reachability-metadata-path <reach-meta-repo>] [--metrics-repo-path <metrics-repo>] [--docs-path <docs>] [--strategy-name NAME]`\n3793:  import org.graalvm.buildtools.gradle.tasks.BuildNativeImageTask\n3794:  import org.graalvm.buildtools.gradle.tasks.NativeRunTask\n3795:  import org.gradle.api.tasks.PathSensitivity\n3809:  def skipJacoco = providers.gradleProperty(\"skipJacoco\").map { it.toBoolean() }.getOrElse(false)\n3863:  // gradle check\n3874:  /home/mihailo/.gradle/caches/modules-2/metadata-2.107/descriptors/com.oracle.oci.sdk/oci-java-sdk-addons-oke-workload-identity/3.72.0/26c913274550a0b2221f47a0fe2d2358/descriptor.bin\n3875:  /home/mihailo/.gradle/caches/modules-2/metadata-2.107/descriptors/com.oracle.oci.sdk/oci-java-sdk-addons-oke-workload-identity/3.72.2/26c913274550a0b2221f47a0fe2d2358/descriptor.bin\n3876:  /home/mihailo/.gradle/caches/modules-2/metadata-2.107/descriptors/com.oracle.oci.sdk/oci-java-sdk-addons-oke-workload-identity/3.72.1/26c913274550a0b2221f47a0fe2d2358/descriptor.bin\n3877:  /home/mihailo/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.oracle.oci.sdk/oci-java-sdk-addons-oke-workload-identity/3.72.0/79559782f213f5f91b5264d3d54e