{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"agent_message","text":"## Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed during library-preparation preflight (`test_generation_failed`). Preserved work: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7759-library-new-request-com.oracle.saas.spectra.platform-spectra-java-client-addons-workload-identity-0.0.174-8725daed\n\nThe likely blocker is artifact access: Maven Central returned no artifact/404, while Oracle Maven redirected the POM request to a secure endpoint that returned HTTP 401 Basic authentication. The generated discovery JSON therefore has `N/A` for repository, source, test, and documentation URLs; no generated test or final metadata directory is present, and no coverage or run metrics are available.\n\nInspect:\n- `logs/com.oracle.saas.spectra.platform:spectra-java-client-addons-workload-identity:0.0.174/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\n- `logs/com.oracle.saas.spectra.platform:spectra-java-client-addons-workload-identity:0.0.174/library-preparation-preflight/pi-generation-2026-07-11T18-07-31-086677Z.log`\n\n- Provide authenticated Oracle Maven access or an accessible repository containing the POM, JAR, sources, and tests.\n- Confirm the artifact is a supported JVM/Native Image target and document any required runtime setup.\n- Resume generation from the preserved branch after access and provenance are available."}}
